#: ../../source/administration/custom-terms-of-service.rst:8
msgid ""
"In Mattermost Enterprise Edition E20, you can outline custom Terms of "
"Service for your team members to accept before they can access Mattermost"
" on web, desktop or mobile."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/custom-terms-of-service.rst:11
msgid "Configuring Terms of Service"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/custom-terms-of-service.rst:13
msgid "To enable custom terms of service:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/custom-terms-of-service.rst:15
msgid ""
"Go to **System Console > Customization > Custom Terms of Service** in "
"prior versions or **System Console > Compliance > Custom Terms of "
"Service** in versions after 5.12."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/custom-terms-of-service.rst:16
msgid "Set **Enable Custom Terms of Service** to **true**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/custom-terms-of-service.rst:17
msgid ""
"Set **Custom Terms of Service Text** which contains your terms. Note that"
" Markdown-formatting, including lists, headings and bolding, is "
"supported."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/custom-terms-of-service.rst:18
msgid ""
"Set **Re-Acceptance Period**, which sets the number of days before Terms "
"of Service acceptance expires, and the terms must be re-accepted. Set to "
"0 if you don't want your terms to expire."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/custom-terms-of-service.rst:19
msgid "Click **Save**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/custom-terms-of-service.rst:21
msgid ""
"Once saved, all users must accept the terms of service by clicking **I "
"Agree** next time they log in, or on the next page refresh. If they do "
"not accept, they will be logged out."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/custom-terms-of-service.rst:25
msgid ""
"If you make an update to your Terms of Service, make sure to update your "
"terms of service link at **System Console > Customization > Legal and "
"Support > Terms of Service link** in prior versions or **System Console >"
" Site Configuration > Customization** in versions after 5.12."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/custom-terms-of-service.rst:27
msgid ""
"This link is presented to all users on each log in, and is easily "
"accessible to end users after accepting the terms."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/custom-terms-of-service.rst:30
msgid "Frequently Asked Questions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/custom-terms-of-service.rst:33
msgid "What happens if I update my terms of service text?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/custom-terms-of-service.rst:35
msgid ""
"There will be no impact to your end users. Users will simply be required "
"to accept the new terms on next login or page refresh."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/custom-terms-of-service.rst:38
msgid "How do I know if my users accepted the terms of service?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/custom-terms-of-service.rst:40
msgid ""
"Each time a user agrees to the terms of service, the agreement is "
"recorded in the database:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/custom-terms-of-service.rst:42
msgid ""
"A new field ``AcceptedServiceTermsId`` in the **Users** table indicates "
"the most recent terms of service the user has accepted."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/custom-terms-of-service.rst:43
msgid ""
"Each time a user accepts the terms, the action is recorded in the "
"**Audits** table, containing the username, timestamp of acceptance, and "
"other relevant information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/custom-terms-of-service.rst:46
msgid "Why isn't this feature in Team Edition for GDPR compliance?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/custom-terms-of-service.rst:48
msgid ""
"Terms of service is presented to users on login and account creation, and"
" available to users at all times in the link specified at **System "
"Console > Customization > Legal and Support > Terms of Service link** in "
"prior versions or **System Console > Site Configuration > Customization**"
" in versions after 5.12."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/custom-terms-of-service.rst:50
msgid ""
"This feature is intended to meet compliance requirements for large "
"Enterprise companies."
msgstr ""

